    "body": "### Problem\n\nCreating a hl for `MsgArea` when a message is currently shown, clears messages.\r\nSince most colorschemes set this hl group, this will effectively not show some messages during startup to the user.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim -u repro.lua`\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"MsgArea\", { fg = \"red\" })\r\nprint(\"foobar\")\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`foobar` should be shown, but it's not.\r\nCommenting the `set_hl` line shows the correct behavior\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndidn't test\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbob",
